headline: Renting in San Francisco turns cutthroat as AI jobs boom collides with low supply
summary: After a long post-pandemic slump, San Francisco is booming again. Competition to land an apartment is stiff.

headline: The Guns N’ Roses-inspired company helping to make job search less soul-crushing
summary: As a fan of rock band Gun N’ Roses, Jérémy Clédat wanted to start his company with a name that resonated with the global job search market.
